# Skills Convention (Anthropic standard)

## Struktura skill

```
skills/<skill-name>/                  # kebab-case
├── SKILL.md                          # REQUIRED — main instructions
├── assets/                           # static resources (templates, examples)
│   ├── template-hero.html
│   ├── template-features.html
│   └── ...
└── references/                       # additional context (markdown OK)
    ├── inspiration.md
    ├── content-patterns.md
    └── target-audience.md
```

## SKILL.md frontmatter (REQUIRED)

```yaml
---
name: roduq-saas-landing          # kebab-case, matches folder name
description: |
  Generate SaaS landing page z hero + features + pricing + CTA + testimonials + FAQ.
  Use when user wants conversion-focused page dla software product.
when_to_use: |
  - User mentions "SaaS landing", "product page", "software website"
  - Brief includes pricing tiers, feature comparisons
  - Target audience = decision-makers (CTOs, founders, ops)
model_hint: "anthropic"             # preferred provider gdy multiple available
---
```

## SKILL.md body structure

```markdown
# <Skill Display Name>

## Instructions

Step-by-step procedure agent follows. Reference assets/ files via relative path.

## Examples

Concrete input → output examples z fixtures.

## Output contract

Każda skill produkuje 4 files w `~/.roduq/output/<client-id>/`:
- `tokens.json` — design tokens (validated z JSON Schema v1)
- `sections.json` — Payload-ready block configs
- `content.json` — draft copy (PL + EN per section)
- `design-system.md` — human-readable summary

Patrz `.cursor/rules/004-file-protocol.mdc` dla schema details.
```

